  "prompt": "What is the best way to find out how many people search for specific keywords online?",
  "response": "To find out how many people search for specific keywords online, you can use several tools and methods:\n\n1. Google Keyword Planner\n- Free tool within Google Ads\n- Provides search volume data\n- Requires a Google Ads account (no need to run ads)\n\n2. SEMrush\n- Paid professional SEO tool\n- Offers detailed keyword research\n- Provides search volume, difficulty, and trends\n\n3. Ahrefs\n- Comprehensive SEO tool\n- Gives keyword search volume and difficulty\n- Offers detailed keyword insights\n\n4. Ubersuggest\n- Free and paid versions available\n- Shows monthly search volume\n- Provides keyword suggestions\n\n5. Google Trends\n- Free tool by Google\n- Shows relative search interest\n- Compares keyword popularity over time\n\n6. Answer the Public\n- Free keyword research tool\n- Shows related questions and search queries\n- Helpful for understanding search intent\n\n7. Moz Keyword Explorer\n- Part of Moz Pro suite\n- Provides search volume and difficulty\n- Offers keyword suggestions\n\nEach tool has strengths and limitations, so using multiple sources can give you a more comprehensive view of keyword search volumes.",
